HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 584
By Cepicky
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate the Columbia
Academy girls' cross country team, 2024 TSSAA
Division II, Class A state champions.
WHEREAS, it is appropriate that we honor those Tennessee students who, through their
athletic prowess, have achieved the pinnacle of success and serve as exceptional ambassadors
of the Volunteer State; and
WHEREAS, one such group of estimable individuals is the Columbia Academy girls'
cross country team, which won the 2024 TSSAA Division II, Class A state championship, the
first such title in school history; and
WHEREAS, state championships are achieved only through hard work, dedication, and
the commitment to working together as a team and excelling with a cooperative spirit; the
Columbia Academy Bulldogs exhibited each of these rare qualities during their championship
season; and
WHEREAS, the Columbia Academy girls' cross country team won the 2024 state title
under the astute leadership of Head Coach Brady Henson and assistant coaches Nathan Miller,
Ashley Miller, and David Craig; and
WHEREAS, during the championship competition, held at Sanders Ferry Park in
Hendersonville on November 8, 2024, the Bulldogs displayed the tenacity, camaraderie, and
skill befitting the state's finest athletic teams; and
WHEREAS, Columbia Academy posted an average time of 20:36:81 to win the state
championship with 44 points, besting their closest opponent by 15 points; and
WHEREAS, in the five-kilometer race, Gracie Orton was state runner-up, placing second
overall with a time of 19:39.28; Presley Miller placed fourth at 20:09.76; Janie Reames placed
