WHEREAS, other contributing and supportive members of the Columbia Academy team
were Emma Bookout, Braelyn Henry, Annyston Barker, Ella Buckley, Lakelyn Haley, Ava
Buckley, and Jayden Massey; and
WHEREAS, the Columbia Academy Bulldogs' noteworthy achievement is a tremendous
source of pride for their families, their classmates, and their entire community; and
WHEREAS, we find it appropriate to acknowledge and applaud the members of the girls'
cross country team of Columbia Academy for serving as exemplars of the high quality of the
youth of Tennessee; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate the members and coaches of the Columbia
Academy girls' cross country team on winning the 2024 TSSAA Division II, Class A state
championship and extend to them our best wishes for continued success in all their future
endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
